com.ualberta.cmput301w17t22.moodswing

Class MoodEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ualberta.cmput301w17t22.moodswing.MoodEvent

  • public class MoodEvent
extends java.lang.Object
    A MoodEvent is an object that is posted to the MoodSwing app and displayed on certain feeds within it.

    A MoodEvent contains the posting participant's username, emotional state, the date the mood event was created, a short explanation trigger for the mood event, a social situation that contributed to the mood event, and the lastKnownLocation of the mood event.

    Version:
    2017-02-19
    Author:
    Fred, bbest
